<section id="fs-idm395901088" class="problem-set-a">
<title>Problem Set A</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm409216768">
<problem id="fs-idm681544080">
<para id="fs-idm401344464"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67924"/>The partnership of Tatum and Brook shares profits and losses in a 60:40 ratio respectively after Tatum receives a 10,000 salary and Brook receives a 15,000 salary. Prepare a schedule showing how the profit and loss should be divided, assuming the profit or loss for the year is:</para>
<list id="fs-idm414526720" list-type="enumerated" number-style="upper-alpha">
<item>$40,000</item>
<item>$25,000</item>
<item>($5,000)</item>
</list>
<para id="fs-idm382094512">In addition, show the resulting entries to each partner’s capital account. Tatum’s capital account balance is $50,000 and Brook’s is $60,000.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
</section>
<section id="fs-idm416422784" class="problem-set-b">
